## Overview

**Wesley Anthony Brown** (April 3, 1927 – May 22, 2012) was a pioneering African-American naval officer and civil engineer. He holds the distinction of being the first African American to graduate from the United States Naval Academy (USNA) in Annapolis, Maryland, achieving this historic milestone in 1949. Throughout his 20-year career in the U.S. Navy's Civil Engineer Corps, Brown contributed to significant infrastructure projects worldwide and later served as a facilities planner at Howard University.

