## Early Life and Education

Wesley Brown was born in Baltimore, Maryland, and raised in Washington, D.C., where his father delivered groceries and his mother worked in a dry-cleaning shop. He graduated from Dunbar High School in 1944, where he served as Cadet Corps Battalion Commander during his senior year. After high school, Brown attended Howard University before receiving an appointment to the U.S. Naval Academy in 1945, nominated by New York Congressman Adam Clayton Powell Jr. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}

