## Naval Academy Experience

Upon entering the Naval Academy, Brown became the sixth African American admitted but the first to graduate. He faced significant racial hostility, including isolation and harassment from fellow midshipmen. Despite these challenges, Brown excelled academically and athletically, participating in cross-country and track teams alongside future President Jimmy Carter. He credited his perseverance to supportive classmates and a personal commitment to take "one day at a time." :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}

