## Post-Navy Career and Legacy

Following his military service, Brown worked as a facilities planner at Howard University from 1976 to 1988. He remained active in mentoring and motivational speaking, particularly during Black History Month, inspiring students and midshipmen with his experiences. In 2008, the U.S. Naval Academy honored him by dedicating the Wesley Brown Field House, a state-of-the-art athletic facility, recognizing his trailblazing contributions. :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}

